President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. These include R. Gil Kerlikowske as Commissioner of Customs in the Department of Homeland Security, Lieutenant General Frank G. Klotz as Under Secretary for Nuclear Security and Administrator for Nuclear Security of the National Nuclear Security Administration in the Department of Energy, and Sarah Sewall as Under Secretary of State for Civilian Security, Democracy, and Human Rights in the Department of State. Other nominees include Suzanne E. Spaulding, Kathryn D. Sullivan, Karen Dynan, Peter J. Kadzik, Anne W. Patterson, Linda Spoonster Schwartz, Stevan E. Bunnell, Steven Croley, Richard F. Griffin, Jr., Deborah A. P. Hersman, Christopher A. Hart, Dwight L. Bush, Sr., Pamela K. Hamamoto, and Matthew T. Harrington. President Obama stated that these individuals bring a wealth of experience and talent to their new roles and he looks forward to working with them in the future.